examples.en: I bumped into my ex in town.
My car bumped into the tree.
She bumped her arm on the table.
Then he bumped me against the wall.
Guess who I bumped into on the way home.
They bumped into us from behind.
I've bumped into the door and hurt my knee.
The loss bumped us out of first place.
The TV show will be bumped to a new time.
I bumped into an old friend in town today.
Prices were bumped up by 10 percent last week.
He almost bumped into me as he rushed past.
I have a bruise from where I bumped my head.
He bumped into someone and mumbled an apology.
The flight was overbooked, and I got bumped off.
He bumped into some lady walking to the bus stop.
I bumped into her quite by chance in Oxford Street.
Another skater bumped into him and knocked him off balance.
The old man who owned the jewels was bumped off by the thieves.
The roof was so low he bumped his head (=his head hit the roof).
The reforms bumped many families off the state-provided healthcare list.
